benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Retrieve invoice item custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios covered: successful retrieval with default audit and with audit levels FULL, MINIMAL, NONE.
Empty Response scenario covered: item with no custom fields returns empty JSON array (TC04).
Query Parameters handling covered: multiple audit values (FULL, MINIMAL, NONE) via TC01-03 and TC05; extra query parameter ignored (TC11); invalid audit value (TC19).
Error handling covered: invalid invoiceItemId format (TC06/TC10/TC21), non-existent item (TC07), system errors (TC09 503, TC20 503).
Performance and large data handling covered: large dataset test (TC12), concurrency (TC15), and timeout (TC16).
Regression and compatibility covered: regression test for missing audit parameter (TC13) and backward compatibility test (TC14).
Security considerations covered: XSS attempt in invoiceItemId (TC21).
Accessibility considerations covered: machine readable JSON and descriptive field names (TC22).
Edge case coverage covered: missing invoiceItemId in path (TC18).
gaps: Pagination for large datasets is not tested (no explicit pagination tests).
Rate limiting / throttling scenarios are not tested.
Caching behavior (ETag / Cache-Control) is not tested.
403 Forbidden scenarios are not explicitly tested (only 401 Unauthorized covered).
Limited Accept-header variations beyond TC14 are not deeply tested for backward compatibility.
Other internal server errors (e.g., 500) are not explicitly tested beyond 503.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests for /invoiceItems/{id}/customFields with page/size parameters to verify proper pagination behavior and responses.
Add rate limiting tests to ensure the API handles bursts gracefully (e.g., simulate multiple concurrent requests within a short window).
Add tests validating caching headers like ETag and Cache-Control on responses.
Add a test covering 403 Forbidden to validate authorization boundaries for restricted users.
Expand Accept header variation tests to better validate backward compatibility across more client versions.
Include tests for 500 Internal Server Error scenarios to cover unexpected server failures beyond 503.
